Package: reverse-tree
Architecture: all
Depends: python3 (>= 3.6), ${python3:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Create directory structures from tree format files
 reverse-tree is a command-line tool that creates directory structures
 from tree-format files. It's the reverse of the tree command.
 .
 Features:
  - Convert tree-format text into real directory structures
  - Automatically creates directories and empty files
  - Flexible input and output options